benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/block - Block a bundle

covered: POST Method - Valid Payload: TC01 and TC02 verify creation with required and optional payloads.
POST Method - Invalid Payload: TC08 covers malformed body; TC19/TC20 cover injection/XSS invalid inputs.
POST Method - Validation: Tests covering date format (TC11), missing required headers (TC09), missing body (TC10), invalid bundleId format (TC06).
POST Method - Large Payloads: TC16 covers very large payloads within allowed limits.
POST Method - Query Parameters: Variations with query params (TC02, TC04, TC12).
POST Method - Not Found / Wrong Bundle: 404 for non-existent bundle (TC07) and 404 when no bundles exist (TC05).
POST Method - Server Unavailability / Dependency Errors: TC17 (service down) and TC28 (dependent service error).
POST Method - Concurrency / Network issues: TC21 (network retry) and TC22 (concurrent requests).
POST Method - Security / Input Sanitization: TC19 (injection) and TC20 (XSS).
POST Method - Regression / Compatibility: TC23, TC24.
gaps: Duplicate Submission / Idempotency not covered (repeated submissions handling).
Explicit 403 Forbidden scenarios for insufficient permissions not explicitly tested (beyond 401/400 cases).
Internal Server Error (500) scenario not explicitly tested (only 502/503 covered in integration case TC28).
recommendations: Add a test for duplicate submissions to validate idempotency behavior.
Add rate limiting/throttling tests to verify handling under burst traffic.
Add tests for caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) and caching behavior.
Add explicit 403 Forbidden tests to cover insufficient permissions scenarios separate from authentication failures.
Add a dedicated 500 Internal Server Error scenario (simulate DB/service failure) to ensure proper 500 handling.
